<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Duh</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-22 06:00:19</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>If you think a shaman's prime role in a group is to buff your stats, you need to take another look at their spell list, and learn that stats don't do jack.<BR>
<BR>
Shaman's MAIN role in a group is to slow the mob.  Nobody does it better.  High level shaman spells can slow a mob up to 85%, and if you're only slowing it by 30%, that's a TON of extra damage your group is taking for no reason.  </font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
