<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Slymm</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-11-18 05:23:10</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>FBSS = Flowing Black Silk Sash<BR>
<BR>
Rare off the Frenzied Ghoul in Lguk. <BR>
<BR>
you can look it up for the full stats, but I believe it's 0.1 wt, 0ac, 21% perm haste*, waist slot.<BR>
<BR>
* The haste on the sash (and most other haste items) is one of the most hotly debated topics in the game. The FBSS is nice, but as far as haste gear goes, its easily one of the worst, and right so, as its one of the easiest to get, with the others coming deep from the 50+ dungeons in Kunark, from the planes (even PoS tests) or dragon/gods. Other haste items usually have ac and stats, not to mention a better haste percentage.<BR>
<BR>
All that said, I'd still love one.<BR>
<BR>
Slymm Pikkins<BR>
30th Rogue of Tarew Marr<BR>
Dragonkin</font></td></tr></table>
